# Project 3 — Hotel Revenue Database + Power BI Dashboard

This project loads historical hotel booking data from Excel into a PostgreSQL database running in Docker.  
The database is designed with a main `bookings` table and lookup tables for meal costs and market segment discounts.  
The goal is to build a clean SQL layer for analytics and then create a Power BI dashboard on top.

## Tech Stack
- Python (pandas, psycopg)
- PostgreSQL (Docker)
- Power BI (dashboard)

## Dataset
Excel workbook includes:
- `2018`, `2019`, `2020` sheets (booking-level data)
- `meal_cost` sheet (meal code -> cost)
- `market_segment` sheet (segment -> discount)

## Project Structure
- `docker-compose-hotel.yml` — starts PostgreSQL container
- `create_hotel_table.py` — creates tables + foreign key constraints
- `load_lookups.py` — loads lookup tables from Excel (`meal_cost`, `market_segment_discount`)
- `load_bookings.py` — loads all booking rows (2018–2020) into `bookings`
- `load_revenue.py` — calculates revenue by hotel type and year and stores it in `hotel_revenue`
